Business Brief -- Infinity Broadcasting Corp.:
   Operator of Radio Stations
   Posts Fourth-Quarter Profit
Revenue rose 8% to $32.6 million from $30.3 million.
   For the year, Infinity narrowed its loss to $6 million, or
92 cents a share, from $39.7 million, or $8.83 a share, in
1990. In 1991 it benefited from an extraordinary gain of $18
million as a result of the purchase of about $87 million of
junk bonds at a significant discount.